{"key":"processedPost-17926131","value":{"id":17926131,"first":17925217,"last":17926203,"when":1362797117,"utime":"03/09/13 04:45 AM","cleanedPost":"Fungus gnats breed in your houseplants, especially during winter.&nbsp; Find out which one and use a shop-vac to get all the loose topsoil off, which takes most of the gnats and eggs with it.&nbsp; Then, pour 3% peroxide over the soil to saturate it and run out the bottom.&nbsp; This will kill the gnat larvae.<br />Finally, replace the soil you vacuumed off with fresh potting soil.<br />They won't breed in your substrates unless they're too wet and won't colonize.<br />RR"}}